# Falcon Dash Environment Variables
#
# No environment variables are required when the OpenClaw gateway runs locally.
# The dashboard reads gateway configuration from ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json.
#
# For remote gateway development (gateway on another machine):
# Copy this file to .env and set both variables below.
#
# GATEWAY_URL=ws://192.168.x.x:28789
# GATEWAY_TOKEN=your-gateway-token
# OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=your-gateway-token  # alias used by managed deployments
#
# Remote gateway setup (one-time, on the gateway machine):
#   1. Set gateway.bind: "lan" in ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json
#   2. Add gateway.controlUi.allowedOrigins: ["http://localhost:5173"]
#   3. Approve dev machine pairing: openclaw devices approve
#
# Gateway Control UI path — when set, the Control UI iframe loads from this
# same-origin path (routed to gateway via Cloudflare Tunnel) instead of the
# SvelteKit HTTP proxy. This enables WebSocket support in the Control UI.
# GATEWAY_CONTROL_PATH=/setup
#
# Sentry error tracking (optional):
# SENTRY_DSN=https://examplePublicKey@o0.ingest.sentry.io/0
# SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=production
#
# Sentry source map upload (optional, for production builds):
# Requires a Sentry auth token with project:releases and org:read scopes.
# When set, source maps are generated, uploaded, then deleted from the build.
# SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=sntrys_...
# SENTRY_ORG=your-org
# SENTRY_PROJECT=falcon-dash
